  <exercise xml:id="splita-visual">
    <introduction>
      <p>
        In this exercise, we will look at how to visually identify the different measurements involved the splitting of the acceleration vector. While each of <m>\va</m>, <m>\vT</m>, <m>\vN</m>, <m>a_{\vT} \vT</m>, and <m>a_{\vN} \vN</m> are drawn, the colors have been randomized so you will need to look at how each element is related to the motion along the curve. 
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          The vectors <m>\va</m>, <m>\vT</m>, <m>\vN</m>, <m>a_{\vT} \vT</m>, and <m>a_{\vN} \vN</m> are drawn in different colors in <xref ref="splita-random1" />. Match each color with proper vector.
        </p>
        <figure xml:id="splita-random1">
          <caption> A 2D curve with splitting of acceleration shown using randomized colors</caption>
          <image width="55%" xml:id="img-splita-random1">
            <description><p>A 2D curve with splitting of acceleration shown using randomized colors</p></description>
            <sageplot>
              var('t')
              r2(t)=(3*t^2*sin(3-2*t),t-cos(2+t))
              c=['purple', 'red', 'blue', 'orange', 'green']
              tval=2/3
              rescale=1/3
              pos=r2(tval)
              plot8=parametric_plot(r2(t),(t,0,1.3),aspect_ratio=1,color="black",thickness=2,axes=False)
              plot8+=point(pos,color="black",size=30)
              v2(t)=diff(r2,t)
              a2(t)=diff(v2,t)
              vt=v2(tval)
              at=a2(tval)
              T=vt/norm(vt)
              aTT=(at*T)*T
              aN=sqrt(norm(at)^2-(at*T)^2)
              aNN=at-aTT
              N=(1/aN)*aNN
              offset=0.25
              plot8+=arrow(pos,pos+T,color=c[0],thickness=2)
              plot8+=arrow(pos,pos+N,color=c[1],thickness=2)
              plot8+=arrow(pos,pos+rescale*aTT,color=c[2])
              plot8+=arrow(pos,pos+rescale*aNN,color=c[3])
              plot8+=arrow(pos,pos+rescale*at,color=c[4])
              plot8  
            </sageplot>
          </image>
        </figure>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          The vectors <m>\va</m>, <m>\vT</m>, <m>\vN</m>, <m>a_{\vT} \vT</m>, and <m>a_{\vN} \vN</m> are drawn in different colors in <xref ref="splita-random2" />. Match each color with proper vector.
        </p>
